`,e.jsx(o.p,{children:"One of the biggest challenges facing the adoption of pay-per-tool is the cost of operations combined with onchain costs and limits. With gas fees on chains like Solana and Base—both of which are two of the more popular x402 chains today—being around ~$0.001 for a single transaction, that is close to 15% of the actual cost of the payment being around $0.01, which is the most common cost for an x402 payment today."}),`
